<p class="eyebrow">Open Source</p>
<h1>Reference tools for the communications problems we solve in production.</h1>
<p class="lede">VoiceTel open-source work helps customers inspect, test, and integrate the same patterns the platform supports: voice markup examples, SDK host overrides, SIP integrations, SDN appliance assets, and operational tooling.</p>
<p class="hero-actions">
	<a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/voicetel">Browse GitHub</a>
	<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/contact/">Suggest a project</a>
</p>

<section class="section-block" data-section-type="project-types">
	<h2>What to publish</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>VoiceML examples</strong> — Small, readable call flows for IVR, click-to-call, recordings, conferences, queues, and webhook validation.</li>
		<li><strong>SDK migration helpers</strong> — Minimal host-override examples and tests for supported helper-library patterns.</li>
		<li><strong>SIP integration guides</strong> — Example configuration for Asterisk, FreePBX, FreeSWITCH, FusionPBX, SBCs, and firewalls.</li>
		<li><strong>SDN appliance assets</strong> — Image references, deployment notes, and troubleshooting workflows where publicly releasable.</li>
		<li><strong>Operational tools</strong> — Trace analyzers, webhook validators, rate-modeling helpers, and support utilities.</li>
	</ul>
</section>

